text: Tas is an agricultural clan of the Indian and Pakistani Gurjar ethnic community in Indian Punjab. Tas Gujjars are followers of Hinduism, Islam, and Sikhism. ==Geographical distribution== They inhabit several different Indian states, including Rajasthan, Haryana, Uttar Pradesh, Punjab, Madhya Pradesh, Uttarakhand, Jammu and Kashmir, Gujarat, Himachal Pradesh and Dehli. In Pakistan they inhabit Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, Azad Kashmir, Balochistan and Punjab (especially in Gujrat, Lahore and Gujranwala districts) provinces of Pakistan. ==References== Category:Gurjar clans Category:Gurjar clans of India Category:Gurjar clans of Pakistan Category:Social groups of Gujarat Category:Social groups of Rajasthan
